# Job Search Profile

> **Edit this file with your own background and target roles.** The pipeline
> uses it to give Claude context when summarizing job descriptions and ranking
> matches. The more specific you are, the better the matching.
>
> **How the pipeline uses this file.** There are two scoring stages. Stage 1
> (`parse_and_score.py`) is mechanical — it scores every job on title keywords,
> salary, recency, and location, and uses this file only loosely (for search
> queries and constraints). Stage 2 (`apply_profile_fit.py`) runs *after*
> enrichment splices full descriptions into Strong-tier jobs: an agent reads
> this entire profile alongside each job's title + description and emits a
> 0–5 fit score that gets added to the total. So prose in `Target role profile`
> directly shapes Stage 2 rankings — the more concrete you are about scope,
> stage, sector, and what's a non-fit, the better.

## Background
- **Current role:** {{your current job title and company, e.g. "Marketing Manager at Acme Corp"}}
- **Total experience:** {{years and a one-line summary, e.g. "8 years across B2B SaaS marketing"}}
- **Education:** {{degree, school, year}}

## Target roles
List the role titles and levels you're targeting. Be inclusive — the pipeline
runs a separate search per role. Examples:
- {{Senior Marketing Manager}}
- {{Director of Marketing}}
- {{Head of Growth}}

### Target role profile
A short prose description of what the ideal role actually looks like. The
pipeline's stage-2 profile-fit agent reads this when scoring Strong-tier
matches against full job descriptions, so be specific about scope, company
stage, sector preferences, and the kind of work you want to be doing.

Example: "Senior IC or first-time lead at a Series A–C B2B SaaS company.
Owns a full marketing function or a major channel end-to-end. Mission-aligned
with developer tools, fintech, or climate preferred. Not a fit for agency
roles or very early-stage (pre-seed) companies."

> **Multiple resume framings?** If you have more than one resume for different
> role types (e.g. Chief of Staff vs. Program Manager vs. Partnerships), repeat
> this "Target role profile" block per framing with its own highlighted skills
> and target-role description. See `profiles/elissa/profile.md` for an example.

## Core skills / specialties
What you bring to a role — used by the scorer to weight title relevance.
Examples: `B2B demand gen`, `SEO`, `paid acquisition`, `Hubspot`, `lifecycle marketing`.

## Search constraints
- **Locations:** {{e.g. New York, NY · Remote (US) · Boston, MA}}
- **Salary floor:** {{e.g. $130,000 base — filters out junior roles}}
- **Job type:** {{Full-time / Contract / Either}}
- **Anything else:** {{e.g. "must offer health benefits", "no agencies", etc.}}
